#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:4
msgid "Structure"
msgstr "结构"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:9
msgid "Bézier Curves"
msgstr "贝塞尔曲线"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:11
msgid ""
"The main elements used in editing Bézier curves are the control points "
"and handles. A segment (the actual curve) is found between two control "
"points. The handles define the curvature of the segment."
msgstr ""
"用于编辑Bézier曲线的主要元素是控制点和手柄。在两个控制点之间找到一段（实"
"际的曲线）。手柄定义段的曲率。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:15
msgid ""
"In the image below, the control points can be found in the middle of the "
"pink line, while the handles comprise the extensions from the control "
"point. The arrows visualize the normals of the curve, which indicate i."
"a. the direction and the tilt."
msgstr ""
"在下图中，可以在粉红色的线中间找到控制点，而手柄则由控制点的扩展组成。箭"
"头表示曲线的法线，这表示它的方向和倾斜程度。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:23
msgid "Bézier Curve in Edit Mode."
msgstr "编辑模式下的贝塞尔曲线。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:29
msgid "Handle Types"
msgstr "手柄类型"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:31
msgid ""
"There are four Bézier curve handle types. They can be accessed by "
"pressing :kbd:`V` and selecting from the list that appears, or by "
"pressing the appropriate hotkey combination."
msgstr ""
"有四个Bézier曲线手柄类型。可以通过按下 :kbd:`V` 并从出现的列表中进行选"
"择，或者按下相应的快捷键组合。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:38
msgid "Bézier Curve Handle Types."
msgstr "Bézier曲线手柄类型。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:45
msgid "Automatic :kbd:`V-A`"
msgstr "自动 :kbd:`V-A`"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:44
msgid ""
"This handle has a completely automatic length and direction which is set "
"by Blender to ensure the smoothest result. These handles convert to "
"*Aligned* handles when moved. (Yellow handles)."
msgstr ""
"这个手柄有一个完全自动的长度和方向，由Blender设置，以确保最流畅的结果。这"
"些手柄在移动时转换为 *Aligned* 句柄。（黄色手柄）。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:49
msgid "Vector :kbd:`V-V`"
msgstr "方向 :kbd:`V-V`"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:48
msgid ""
"Both parts of a handle always point to the previous handle or the next "
"handle which allows you to create curves or sections thereof made of "
"straight lines or with sharp corners. Vector handles convert to *Free* "
"handles when moved. (Green handles)."
msgstr ""
"手柄的两个部分总是指向前一个手柄或下一个手柄，它允许您创建由直线或尖角组"
"成的曲线或者其中部分。方向手柄在移动时转换为 *Free* 句柄。 （绿色手柄）。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:52
msgid "Aligned :kbd:`V-L`"
msgstr "对齐 :kbd:`V-L`"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:52
msgid ""
"These handles always lie in a straight line, and give a continuous curve "
"without sharp angles. (Purple handles)."
msgstr ""
"这些手柄总是位于一条直线上，并给出一个没有尖角的连续曲线。（紫色手柄）。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:56
msgid "Free :kbd:`V-F`"
msgstr "自由 :kbd:`V-F`"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:55
msgid "The handles are independent of each other. (Black handles)."
msgstr "这些手柄和其他手柄不相关。（黑色手柄）。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:61
msgid "NURBS"
msgstr "NURBS"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/structure.rst:63
msgid ""
"N.U.R.B.S. is the abbreviation of Non-Uniform Rational B-Splines. One of "
"the major differences between Bézier objects and NURBS objects is that "
"Bézier curves are approximations. For example, a Bézier circle is an "
"*approximation* of a circle, whereas a NURBS circle is an *exact* "
"circle. NURBS theory can be a *very* complicated topic. For an "
"introduction, please consult the `Wikipedia page. <https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/NURBS>`__."
msgstr ""
"NURBS是Non-Uniform Rational B-Splines的缩写。 Bézier对象和NURBS对象之间的"
"主要区别之一是Bézier曲线是近似值。例如，一个贝塞尔圆是一个 *近似* 的圆，"
"而一个NURBS圆是一个 *精确* 的圆。 NURBS理论可能是一个 *非常* 复杂的话题。"
"有关介绍，请参阅维基百科页面.  `<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"NURBS>`__ ."
